name: Horus
title: Horus - The Sky God | Egyptian Mythology
subtitle: God of Kingship, Sky, and Vengeance
shortDescription: Horus is the falcon-headed god of the sky, kingship, and divine right to rule. As the son of Osiris and Isis , he avenged his father's murder by defeating Set and became the divine prototype of the pharaoh. The living king was considered Horus incarnate, while the dead king became Osiris .
